<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-07-17T14:49:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-07-17T14:49:00-05:00" n="327" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d327">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/576.</note>
                        <head>[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-07-17T15:00:00-04:49"><hi rend="smallcaps">July</hi>
                                    17, 1911—3 <hi rend="smallcaps">p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Furniss is advised by the Haitian authorities that a telegram has
                            been received announcing Gonaives in the hands of the revolutionists.
                            The situation makes the presence of a war vessel desirable at Port au
                            Prince.</p>
